From 455c009591e9d9550e7ecba0ce8d88a3e919d347 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Aishwarya R <aisr@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 8 Jul 2025 15:35:41 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] UPSTREAM:DP:CP:wifi: ath12k: Add support for dynamic DSCP
  to TID mapping at vdev level

Currently, ath12k follows fixed DSCP to TID mapping.Add support
for dynamic DSCP to TID mapping based on qos_map_set values from
mac80211

Get qos_map_set events from mac80211 and update TID registers
accordingly.

Caches QoS map if VDEV is not yet created and applies it post-creation.
Manage map_id to uniquely identify DSCP TID mapping tables.

Parse the DSCP exception and UP(User Priority) values, DSCP low
and DSCP high range for every UP from mac80211. Update the TID
registers in vdev level based on the parsed values.

Below is the qos_map_set format
<DSCP Exceptions[DSCP,UP]>,]<UP 0 range[low,high]>,...<UP 7 range[low,high]

Below is the example qos_map_set hostapd configuration
qos_map_set=53,2,22,6,8,15,0,7,255,255,16,31,32,39,255,255,40,47,255,255

Patch-dependency: none
Signed-off-by: Aishwarya R <aisr@qti.qualcomm.com>
